  <bioghist id="aspace_a385ef84ea00c37e32da1c9335c72a7b">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Cornell University Class of 1894.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_18af575aeaddfcc511786b792eb18f00">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Eight manuscript volumes of notes taken by Frederick W. Field while a student at Cornell University. Notebooks concern Minerology (Professor Eakle), Fall '91; Botany (Prentiss), Fall '91; Acoustics and Optics (Nicholls), Spring '92; Physics (Nicholls), History of Architecture (Babcock), and Structural Detail, Fall '92; and Landscape Gardening (Bailey), Fall '93. Also, material relating to the Architectural Club, n.d.</p>  </scopecontent>
